AGI - Tragedy in Alghero: an 8-year-old girl died last night after she was operated in the civil hospital of the Sardinian city. The little girl had been operated on Thursday night in Otorino's department for the removal of tonsils and the surgery was perfectly successful.
&nbsp;
Around 18, yesterday, however, the conditions of the child were suddenly aggravated, apparently following a hemorrhage, reported the Sarda Union. The doctors immediately intervened, doing everything to try to save the small patient native to Villanova Monteleone, but there was nothing to do. The Prosecutor of Sassari opened an investigation.&nbsp;

