AGI - The Municipality of Bari will not be dissolved for mafia infiltrations, as it seemed possible after the investigation "Interno Code", but will see the commissioning of some of its municipalized companies, including Amtab (Mobility and Transportation Bari Spa), and will be sanctioned some municipal employees. Yesterday the term expired to decide on the possible dissolution of the Municipality, in the light of the results of the investigation Internal Code, coordinated by the Anti-Mafia District Direction, that has brought out contacts between mafia and politics that for the polluters have also affected the operation of some municipalities. "We have averted the most nefarious hypothesis, that of the dissolution of the organs of representation," explained the mayor of Bari, Vito Leccese.
&nbsp;
The investigation, which led to the arrest of numerous members of the Mafia families in Bari, highlighted serious interference of organized crime in municipal elections and public companies, such as Amtab, already in judicial administration since 2024. On 2 April last, after the authorization of the court of Bari, the then mayor Antonio Decaro appointed as a member of the Cda lawyer Luca D'Amore, to "strengthening the relationship of collaboration with the judicial authority and speeding up the self-cleaning interventions of the society". The survey unveiled the existence of a political-electoral air conditioning system, with the mafia that would have exercised ingestion also in activities related to the management of waste and public transport.
&nbsp;
In March 2024, 137 precautionary measures for extortion, auction disturbance and electoral ingestion were carried out against affiliates of the mafia organizations, and among them, some have links in companies' participated of the Municipality of Bari. On 19 March 2024, the Ministry of the Interior had specified that the monitoring measures on the administrative activities of the Municipality of Bari were not aimed at dissolution of the Council, but at an in-depth verification of the operation of the local institutions and the companies involved. &nbsp;&nbsp;

